<br>
It is not refering to the National Gaurd or any other formal government organization.  It refers to the responsibilty that a gun owner has to the defense and well being of the community at large.  The &quot;minuteman&quot; militias and even the posse's of the old west are the kind of thing it is referring too.  Being a gun owner inherently involves responsibilty to your community and the government is suppose to regulate in light of that, but it is a very very limited mandate.  The problem is how do we deal with those who DON'T use firearms responsibly w/o impacting those who do. <p><center><font face="lucida handwriting, arial" color="006800" size=+2><b>Radgen Waldjaeger</font></b><br><font face="tempus sans ITC, arial" color="675f00" size=+1><b>Retired Pathfinder of Karana</font><br><font face="tempus sans ITC, arial" color="blue" size=+1>Shining Path</font></b><br><img src=http://radgen.homestead.com/files/tiger_run_md_clr.gif></center>
